 Folder** | 139-multi-model-deep |\n42: | **Completed** | 2026-06-08 |\n43: | **Level** | 2 |\n44: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: <!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n49: ## What Was Built\n50: \n51: <!-- Voice guide:\n52:      Open with a hook: what changed and why it matters. One paragraph, impact first.\n53:      Then use ### subsections per feature. Each subsection: what it does + why it exists.\n54:      Write \"You can now inspect the trace\" not \"Trace inspection was implemented.\"\n55:      NO \"Files Changed\" table for Level 3/3+. The narrative IS the summary.\n56:      For Level 1-2, a Files Changed table after the narrative is fine.\n57:      Reference: specs/system-spec-kit/020-mcp-working-memory-hybrid-rag/implementation-summary.md -->\n58: \n59: [Opening hook: 2-3 sentences on what changed and why it matters. Lead with impact.]\n60: \n61: ### [Feature Name]\n62: \n63: [What this feature does and why it exists. 1-2 paragraphs. Use direct address.\n64: Explain what the user gains, not what files you touched.]\n65: \n66: ### Files Changed\n67: \n68: <!-- Include for Level 1-2. Omit for Level 3/3+ where the narrative carries. -->\n69: \n70: | File | Action | Purpose |\n71: |------|--------|---------|\n72: | [path] | [Created/Modified/Deleted] | [What this change accomplishes] |\n73: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: <!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n78: ## How It Was Delivered\n79: \n80: <!-- Voice guide:\n81:      Tell the delivery story. What gave you confidence this works?\n82:      \"All features shipped behind feature flags\" not \"Feature flags were used.\"\n83:      For Level 1: a single sentence is enough.\n84:      For Level 3+: describe stages (testing, rollout, verification). -->\n85: \n86: [How was this tested, verified and shipped? What was the rollout approach?]\n87: <!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: <!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n92: ## Key Decisions\n93: \n94: <!-- Voice guide: \"Why\" colum