{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780906513952,"sessionID":"ses_159b57c7fffe0UrEO0Gfg5sl7z","part":{"id":"prt_ea64cd61d001oEpQwv6kHHgwnC","messageID":"msg_ea64cc439001aZEv8cHNjCR8Sp","sessionID":"ses_159b57c7fffe0UrEO0Gfg5sl7z","snapshot":"57e96cb89026c99a52d2c29551d3dc095154eb3f","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780906525427,"sessionID":"ses_159b57c7fffe0UrEO0Gfg5sl7z","part":{"id":"prt_ea64ce2bf001Az7IZkQdHpy1Od","messageID":"msg_ea64cc439001aZEv8cHNjCR8Sp","sessionID":"ses_159b57c7fffe0UrEO0Gfg5sl7z","type":"text","text":"A real issue is emerging around the stale-owner reclaim path: the code comment says the owner lease is an `O_EXCL` spawn mutex, but the stale-reclaim branch overwrites the existing lease with tmp+rename and then rereads it. I’m checking counterevidence before recording it as a finding.","time":{"start":1780906517183,"end":1780906525418},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b257cc6b83caeba016a267a151cd481959fec99d7c0a1e1fb","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780906525551,"sessionID":"ses_159b57c7fffe0UrEO0Gfg5sl7z","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_c7rGnAJcNajLhxm35CwJ5eMa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"SPEC_KIT_DB_DIR|MEMORY_DB_PATH|SPECKIT_DB_DIR|resolvedDbDir|dbDir","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server","include":"*.{ts,js,cjs,mjs}"},"output":"Found 238 matches (showing first 100)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/stress_test/durability/daemon-reelection-adoption-live.vitest.ts:\n  Line 57: // Distinct pids holding any *.sqlite* file open under dbDir. One = single writer.\n\n  Line 58: function sqliteOpenerPids(dbDir: string): number[] {\n\n  Line 61:       `lsof +D \"${dbDir}\" 2>/dev/null | awk 'NR>1 && ($9 ~ /\\\\.(db|sqlite|sqlite3)/) {print $2}' | sort -u`,\n\n  Line 69: function buildFakeRoot(): { base: string; sockDir: string; dbDir: string; launcher: string } {\n\n  Line 84:   const dbDir = join(fmcp, 'database');\n\n  Line 85:   mkdirSync(dbDir, { recursive: true, mode: 0o700 });\n\n  Line 88:   return { base, sockDir, dbDir, launcher: join(fbin, 'mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs') };\n\n  Line 129:   paths: { base: string; sockDir: string; dbDir: string; launcher: string },\n\n  Line 138:       SPEC_KIT_DB_DIR: paths.dbDir,\n\n  Line 241:     const dbWriters = sqliteOpenerPids(paths.dbDir);\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/vector-index-store-durability.vitest.ts:\n  Line 56:   delete process.env.MEMORY_DB_PATH;\n\n  Line 63:     process.env.MEMORY_DB_PATH = dbPath;\n\n  Line 75:     process.env.MEMORY_DB_PATH = dbPath;\n\n  Line 89:     process.env.MEMORY_DB_PATH = dbPath;\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/embedders/l