{"type":"text","timestamp":1780906614470,"sessionID":"ses_159b57c7fffe0UrEO0Gfg5sl7z","part":{"id":"prt_ea64e5944001SH8t7W46NT5M5H","messageID":"msg_ea64db75c001D7lEAgj26s8EYe","sessionID":"ses_159b57c7fffe0UrEO0Gfg5sl7z","type":"text","text":"The stale-reclaim mutex issue survived the counterevidence check: the bootstrap lock is not required when artifacts are already ready, `writeLeaseFile` has the same last-writer-wins/reprobe shape, and `launchServer` can still race after the owner lease was briefly observed as self-owned.","time":{"start":1780906613060,"end":1780906614464},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06ca0f2e678a6ef7016a267a750230819184e2d04651dbe73d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
